{"schemaVersion":1,"source":"slidey-capture","viewport":{"width":1600,"height":900,"deviceScaleFactor":1},"startTime":1782277590363,"endTime":1782277636947,"durationMs":46584,"events":[{"type":4,"data":{"href":"file:///Users/brad/code/Kitsoki/.worktrees/kitsoki-github-agent/tools/runstatus/tests/playwright/fixtures/gh-thread.html#","width":1600,"height":900},"timestamp":1782277590363},{"type":2,"data":{"node":{"type":0,"childNodes":[{"type":1,"name":"html","publicId":"","systemId":"","id":2},{"type":5,"textContent":"\n  Static, deterministic replica of the @kitsoki GitHub loop on\n  constructorfabric/Kitsoki — the GitHub side of the kitsoki-github-agent demo\n  (Act 1). One tall single-scroll page with 8 anchored blocks (data-testid hooks),\n  one per storyboard scene: a bug-labelled issue with an @kitsoki mention, the\n  kitsoki ack comment carrying a …/run/<job-id> link, a feature-labelled issue,\n  a PR with red CI, a merge-conflict rebase, a reviewer-comment implement+resolve,\n  a low-confidence guidance request, and a single rolling status comment edited to\n  \"done\" (single-voice, no comment flood).\n\n  It is a FIXTURE, not live GitHub: the cross-site demo must stay deterministic and\n  free (no network, no auth, no real issue churn) — the posture every kitsoki demo\n  uses. The github-demo-issuepr spec drives this over file:// and narrates it with\n  the portable caption + spotlight helpers (the kitsoki tour overlay can't run on a\n  non-kitsoki page). The worked ticket is slidey-128 grid-cards narration-drift, so\n  kitsoki improving slidey is narrated on slidey's own repo — the cleanest dogfood.\n  See .agents/skills/kitsoki-ui-demo/SKILL.md and the gh-issue-review.html sibling.\n","id":3},{"type":2,"tagName":"html","attributes":{"lang":"en"},"childNodes":[{"type":2,"tagName":"head","attributes":{},"childNodes":[{"type":3,"textContent":"\n","id":6},{"type":2,"tagName":"meta","attributes":{"charset":"utf-8"},"childNodes":[],"id":7},{"type":3,"textContent